Advantages of Stack :
âœ… Fast Insertions & Deletions: O(1) time complexity.
âœ… Efficient Memory Usage: No shifting like in arrays.


Disadvantages of Stack :
âŒ Limited Access: Can only access the top element.
âŒ Overflow Risk (Array-Based Stack): If stack is full.
âŒ Underflow Risk: If stack is empty and we try to pop.

Final Thoughts ğŸ’¡
Stacks are super useful for solving problems that follow LIFO (Last-In, First-Out) order.
Whether you're implementing function calls, backtracking, or expression evaluation, stacks make your life much easier!